Title: Stray Cat Strut but it's not swung
Description:
Brian Setzer
Stray Cat Strut
but it's straight, not swung

Although it was originally made famous by the Stray Cats, this is a later re-recording by the original writer/singer/guitarist with another band.

Because deleting 1/3rd of the notes makes it go 33% faster, it's also been time-stretched to slow it back down by 25% to get closer to the original tempo. It's still noticeably faster though.
